40|$|We {{study the}} {{properties}} of the set of binary strings with the relation "the Kolmogorov complexity of x conditional to y is small". We prove that there are pairs of strings which have no <b>greatest</b> common <b>lower</b> <b>bound</b> with respect to this pre-order. We present several examples when the <b>greatest</b> common <b>lower</b> <b>bound</b> exists but its complexity is much less than mutual information (extending G'acs and Korner result [2]) ...|$|R
